-- Flacq of Mauritius to Upgrade Cane-Crushing Mill, l’Express Says
-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 2012-02-15T07:40:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-15/flacq-of-mauritius-to-upgrade-cane-crushing-mill-l-express-says.html
Flacq United Estates Ltd. (FUEL) , a
Mauritian refined white-sugar producer, plans to invest 350
million rupees ($12 million) to increase the cane-crushing
capacity of its mill on the east of the Indian Ocean island,
l’Express said, citing Chief Executive Officer Joseph Vaudin.  The company plans to produce 165,000 metric tons of refined
white sugar this year compared with 162,000 tons a year earlier,
the Port Louis-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in  Port Louis  at 
 kbhuckory@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  